    "name": "John Rae",
    "profile": "Scottish jazz drummer, born June 8th, 1966 in Edinburgh.\r\n[b]Not to be confused with the older Swing and Bop jazz drummer and percussionist [a=Johnny Rae] and the songwriter [a825873]![/b]\r\n\r\nHe recorded his first album at the age of 16, when he was working with saxophonist [a29988]. He recorded many jazz records for [l101418]. He was drummer for the [a2821417] from 2000 to 2003, directed [a5454451] and played with the following bands (to be able to distinguish from the eponymous artist):\r\nThe Troubles, Giant Stepping Stones, John Rae Collective, John Rae's Celtic Feet, The Afro-Celtic Jazz Ensemble and others.\r\nHe collaborated with [a253476], [a196274], [a259092] and many others.\r\nRae moved to New Zealand for a one-year residence and stayed in New Zealand. There he runs a jazz ensemble and teaches at the New Zealand School of Music.",
